# Reelattice git push checklist

Before **committing and pushing** to `main` (or any shared branch), review changelog and whether a **new app release tag** is required.

## When to update changelog

Update `src/lib/changelog.ts` if the push includes anything a user might care about:

- New UI, changed workflows, fixes they would notice
- Website, download, legal, or privacy changes
- Import, playback, export, Cases, Settings, or Help behavior
- Performance or reliability improvements users would feel

Skip changelog-only noise: internal refactors, CI/workflows, dev tooling, `.gitignore`, docs for developers only.

## How to write entries

- **New app release** → new top entry with bumped version (`1.9`, etc.); see `reelattice-release.mdc`.
- **Website-only** on an already-shipped app version → optional website/README note; no app tag unless app code also changed.
- Write for end users in the Help/Changelog voice — what changed and why it matters.
- One clear bullet per user-visible change; group tiny related tweaks into one bullet.
- Date format matches existing entries (`June 2026`).

## When to tag a new app release

If the push includes changes to **shipped desktop app behavior or UI** (`src/`, `src-tauri/`, app assets), you must **release a new version** so in-app updates can deliver it:

1. Complete `reelattice-release.mdc` (version bumps, changelog entry, docs).
2. Commit and `git push origin main`.
3. `git tag vX.Y` and `git push origin vX.Y` — **same session**, do not leave app changes on `main` without a tag.

Website-only pushes (`website/` only, no `src/` changes) do **not** need a new app tag — Vercel deploys from `main` automatically.

## Before push

1. `git diff` — separate **app** vs **website-only** changes.
2. Update `src/lib/changelog.ts` when users should know.
3. If app code changed: bump versions and plan the tag (step 3 above).
4. If update flow or Changelog tab copy changed, skim `src/components/changelog-view.tsx` and `src/components/help-view.tsx`.
5. **Website check** — see below (do not skip on app releases).

Do not push user-facing app work without a changelog entry and release tag.

## Website check (before every push)

The public site at `reelattice.vercel.app` deploys from `main` automatically. Before pushing, confirm the website still matches what you are shipping.

### Always on app release (new tag)

Bump version strings so hero, download, and footer stay in sync:

| File | Field |
|------|-------|
| `website/package.json` | `"version": "X.Y.0"` |
| `website/src/lib/constants.ts` | `APP_VERSION = "X.Y"` |

These must match the app release version in `reelattice-release.mdc`.

### Review copy when user-facing behavior changed

Skim the site for stale or missing marketing copy. Update only when the release adds, removes, or materially changes something visitors would care about:

| Area | File(s) |
|------|---------|
| Hero / live badge | `website/src/components/hero-section.tsx` |
| Download CTA + what's new | `website/src/components/download-section.tsx`, `website/src/lib/release-highlights.ts` |
| Feature cards | `website/src/components/features-section.tsx` |
| Workflow steps | `website/src/components/workflow-section.tsx` |
| App preview / screenshots | `website/src/components/app-preview.tsx` |
| Footer tagline | `website/src/components/site-footer.tsx` |
| Legal pages | `website/src/pages/privacy-page.tsx`, `terms-page.tsx` — only if privacy/terms behavior changed |

There is **no website changelog page** — release notes live in-app (`src/lib/changelog.ts`). The site only needs version bumps plus copy updates when marketed features or workflows change.

### Website-only pushes

If the push is `website/` only (no `src/` app changes): update site copy as needed, bump `APP_VERSION` only when advertising a new downloadable release, and **do not** tag a new app version unless app code also changed.

### Quick decision

- **Bug fix / internal refactor** → version bump only (if releasing), skip marketing copy.
- **New or changed user workflow** (Import, Export, Cases, Settings, etc.) → check hero, features, and workflow sections.
- **Legal / download URL / env** → check `constants.ts`, download section, and legal pages.
